                  <summary><p>The <title xml:lang="ta">Tiruppātiriveṇpā</title> appears to be a poem praising the Lord Śiva of <title xml:lang="ta">Tiruppātirippuliyūr</title>, that is <placeName xml:lang="ta">Pāṭaliputtiram</placeName>, in the undivided South Arcot district of Tamil Nadu. With a commentary interspersed. The text is incomplete. It stops abruptly at stanza no. 79 at the end of the page (U2, <locus facs="85">f37v</locus>).</p>
<p>The <foreign xml:lang="ta">Kāppu</foreign> stanza (unnumbered) is followed by further stanzas, numbered 1‒79. Stanzas are first quoted, then followed by <foreign xml:lang="ta" rend="italic">patavurai</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="ta" rend="italic">poḻippurai</foreign>.</p>
                  </summary>
